# OUT-RUN App - Cursor Rules
# Project: Hebrew-first fitness PWA with Mapbox, Firebase, Zustand

## Language & RTL
- This is a Hebrew-first app. Default text direction is RTL.
- Always set `dir="rtl"` on the outermost container of any new component that renders user-facing text.
- Use Tailwind logical properties: `ms-` (margin-inline-start), `me-` (margin-inline-end), `ps-`, `pe-`, `text-start`, `text-end`. NEVER use `ml-`/`mr-`/`pl-`/`pr-`/`text-left`/`text-right` in RTL contexts.
- Exception: `dir="ltr"` is allowed for numeric displays, code blocks, and admin data tables where LTR is semantically correct.
- The Mapbox RTL text plugin is loaded in `AppMap.tsx` — do not duplicate this initialization.

## Tailwind Best Practices
- Use the project's design tokens from `tailwind.config.ts`: `primary`, `secondary`, `out-blue`, `card-light`, `background-light`.
- Use the shadow system: `shadow-subtle`, `shadow-floating`, `shadow-drawer`, `shadow-premium`, `shadow-card`.
- Use the border-radius scale: `rounded-lg` (10px) for buttons, `rounded-2xl` (14px) for cards, `rounded-3xl` (20px) for sheets/drawers.
- Font stack: `font-sans` uses Simpler Pro. For Hebrew-optimized text use `font-hebrew`.
- Dark mode is `manual` (locked to light). Do NOT add `dark:` variants unless explicitly building a dark-mode component.
- Prefer `clsx()` + `tailwind-merge` for conditional classes. Import from `clsx`.

## One-Card-Only UI Rule
- On the map screen, only ONE bottom overlay may be visible at a time. The priority order is:
  1. Full-screen search (NavigationHub searching) — z-[100]
  2. Navigation sheet (NavigationHub navigating) — z-[60]
  3. Route preview card (RoutePreviewCard) — z-[60]
  4. Workout drawer (WorkoutDrawer, generated routes) — z-[60]
  5. Journey carousel (BottomJourneyContainer, curated routes) — z-40
  6. Park preview card (ParkPreview) — z-30
- When opening a higher-priority overlay, all lower-priority overlays must be hidden.
- The `screen` state machine in `DiscoverLayer` enforces this: SEARCH | NAV | ROUTE_CARD | DISCOVERY.
- Generated routes → WorkoutDrawer. Curated routes → BottomJourneyContainer carousel. This is THE LAW.

## Z-Index Budget (Map UI)
- z-[-1]: ParticleBackground
- z-0: Map canvas (AppMap)
- z-20: Active workout overlay, navigate bottom
- z-30: ParkPreview floating card
- z-40: BottomJourneyContainer, HUD controls
- z-50: Mapbox facility popups
- z-[60]: WorkoutDrawer, NavigationHub (navigating), RoutePreviewCard
- z-[70]: Search bars in discover mode
- z-[90]: JITSetupModal
- z-[95]: Referral toast
- z-[100]: Full-screen overlays (search, sheets, contribution wizard)
- z-[120]: Dev-only banners
- z-[200]: Post-workout summary (RunSummary nested UI)
- DO NOT create new z-index values without updating this table.

## State Management
- Zustand is the state management solution. No Redux, no MobX, no new React Contexts.
- Store ownership: each feature owns its store. Cross-feature reads are allowed; cross-feature writes go through actions/callbacks.
- Existing stores: useAppStore, useUserStore, useMapStore, useSessionStore, useRunningPlayer, useRunningConfigStore, useWeeklyVolumeStore, useActivityStore, useSocialStore, useProgressionStore, usePrivacyStore, useOnboardingStore.
- MapModeContext is the only React Context for map mode routing. LanguageContext wraps useAppStore.

## Architecture Patterns
- Next.js 14 App Router. All client pages use `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`.
- SSR protection: `typeof window !== 'undefined'` guards, `dynamic()` with `ssr: false` for map components, `skipHydration` on persisted stores.
- Feature folder structure: `src/features/{domain}/{admin|client|core}/{components|hooks|services|store|types}`.
- Services import `db` from `@/lib/firebase` and use Firebase modular v9+ API.
- No server sessions — auth is Firebase Auth client-side. Admin RBAC via `checkUserRole()` + `feature-flags.ts`.

## File Boundaries for Parallel Work
- Map & Geo: `src/app/map/`, `src/features/parks/core/` (except drawers)
- UI & Drawers: `src/features/parks/client/`, drawer/sheet components in `src/features/parks/core/components/`
- Firebase & Admin: `src/features/admin/`, `src/app/admin/`, `src/app/api/`, `src/lib/`
- Workout Engine: `src/features/workout-engine/`, `src/app/workouts/`
